<normalizedToken id="C0A814EDEB37B99D33729BFEDA326065" originalValue="Désétangs’" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">Desetangs'</normalizedToken>
Johanniskraut
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="8C0F5346D19F5847D7469F6434FF1A38" pageId="null" pageNumber="716" type="description">
<paragraph id="C128BDFC6753980AEDDE0862AEA96B22" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">
0,3-1 m hoch. Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="D32B05C434CB10110963CE432020E9D6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Hypericaceae" genus="Hypericum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="null" pageNumber="716" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculatum">
<emphasis id="973A349275B2FF00988D621C7E8DF277" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">H. maculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 7c) durch folgende Merkmale: Stengel im obern Teil oft nur 2kantig; 
<normalizedToken id="5806D5CF63F5147785E934A4D10B0773" originalValue="größte" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">groesste</normalizedToken>
Blattbreite meist in der Mitte; 
<normalizedToken id="5646E82EAA4113DCA5C4D7E96CEB2590" originalValue="Kelchblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">Kelchblaetter</normalizedToken>
5-7 mm lang, 
<emphasis id="A97A793EF876924E72C73D3A60A23A35" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">
in eine feine, meist deutlich 
<normalizedToken id="B796ED20C9C19DFFD09295AF1EB1FB55" originalValue="gezähnte" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">gezaehnte</normalizedToken>
Spitze ausgezogen.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E5861EFDE95DF1686AD2EA2A8B293875" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">
<emphasis id="B5B7B926282F70FFCEB395B987A35CB1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="45065DF602BD166B8BA06BB9FAC141CB" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">16:</emphasis>
Ohne weitere Angaben in Schwarz (1965).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F9CA7CE7AC3818677FA87919199EA496" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">
<emphasis id="43DCF965109012B7F318FEA06AB88353" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin. Wie 
<emphasis id="7FC71B5CE4CF2DFC4DFF782693386ECA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">H. erosum</emphasis>
(Nr. 7d).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6A919B8BCA33CB4101BC430180B05F3B" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">
<emphasis id="16BA0011DDC7037FB7D3BC2EEAAAEE72" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">
<pageBreakToken id="FE69E7C8CB6B5F84F6987CFE7898F091" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">Verbreitung</pageBreakToken>
</emphasis>
(
<normalizedToken id="A1EB5555A08E88F8337CB33712154568" originalValue="ungenügend" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">ungenuegend</normalizedToken>
bekannt). 
<emphasis id="1CE88517280C5965B9F86FFC0076645C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">
<normalizedToken id="40065B468DF59881E5782EF7921B954F" originalValue="Westeuropäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">Westeuropaeische</normalizedToken>
Pflanze:
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="07D101F36728EF25EBBFC584E10B00F0" originalValue="Nordwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">Nordwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis England; 
<normalizedToken id="BD29E0C5FE0C109EDC865FE537C3C370" originalValue="ostwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">ostwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Westdeutschland und 
<normalizedToken id="A68FB295F2D7E0588A8230C45044F48D" originalValue="Österreich" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">Oesterreich</normalizedToken>
; 
<normalizedToken id="F4F61F4DD3196609C8F0FD7352C12857" originalValue="südwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">suedwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Spanien und Italien. - Im Gebiet 
<normalizedToken id="821FEAA54997B6D6C851BFC20A89443E" originalValue="nördlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">noerdlich</normalizedToken>
der Alpen und in den 
<normalizedToken id="09877AAFEC98961664112C654101A435" originalValue="nördlichen" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">noerdlichen</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="C06533407E3674BCE22B0B228FD17401" originalValue="Alpentälern" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">Alpentaelern</normalizedToken>
wahrscheinlich verbreitet; nicht 
<normalizedToken id="9465E5AFA758A287FD09F4584492D108" originalValue="häufig" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">haeufig</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E3F65E6FD35BF86A0F38359A219DC12B" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">
<emphasis id="366DEC89D7A7FFF4DFAB5560E0DF4B85" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">Bemerkungen.</emphasis>
Die Angabe in Flora Europaea, Band 2, 1968, wonach 
<taxonomicName id="555798F77F9B9F86DCA7EC0D5EB40819" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Hypericaceae" genus="Hypericum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="null" pageNumber="716" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="desetangsii">
<emphasis id="2BA8A658EA989FAF8A964ED63C3F4BC7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">H. Desetangsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ein Bastard von 
<taxonomicName id="FAB3DB96E723F2038B4BD73F99C0AE1B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Hypericaceae" genus="Hypericum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="null" pageNumber="716" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perforatum">
<emphasis id="C8180E5F1B527E2DE98C683D42D706BF" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">H. perforatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und 
<taxonomicName id="63025C9DD7FE5E2D43E1303447BC28AF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Hypericaceae" genus="Hypericum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="null" pageNumber="716" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculatum">
<emphasis id="027A863BE97FDEF208F68D5987D39170" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">H. maculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sein soll, bedarf experimenteller 
<normalizedToken id="49A0E2F495E14EBB371868372331FAF4" originalValue="Bestätigung" pageId="null" pageNumber="716">Bestaetigung</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
